Class DoNotPropagateEventException

  • java.lang.Object

        • java.lang.RuntimeException
          • org.eclipse.keyple.distributed.spi.DoNotPropagateEventException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class DoNotPropagateEventException
extends java.lang.RuntimeException
    This exception is thrown to indicate to stop the propagation of an event to the remote node.

    You must thrown this exception during the invocation of the method ObservableReaderEventFilter.beforePropagation(ReaderEvent).

    1.0
